column5:
['improved varieties
j. s. 335, macs.1888, phule kalyani (ds228), js.9 305, k.s. 103, leading leading (kds 344)
sowing and cultivation spacing
sowing should be done on the first fortnight of kharabi. sowing 45 x 0.5 cm (heavy land) or 30 x 10 cm (medium land) at the distance.
seeds
use 75-50 kg per hectare for continuous sowing and 45-50 kg per hectare seed for token plantation.
seed treatment - to protect against fungal diseases, take 2.5 gm carbendezme or 5 g trichoderma for one kg of seeds. also, for sterilization of nitrogen, soyabean group raizobium 250 grams + phosphorous soluble bacteria should be boiled to 250 grams per 10 kg seed.']

pusa ruby: it can be taken in three seasons. fruits can be harvested from 45 to 90 days after cultivation. fruit furrows are shaped like furrows, red in color. hectare production 325 quintals
pusa gaurav: this caste shrub is growing fast. the fruits become yellowish crimson after lubrication. the traffic is right. hectare production 400 quintals
pusa shital: planting for the winter season is going well, and fruitful floral goals are red in color. hectare yield 350 quintals
arka gaurav: the fruit is dark red fleshy and comfortable. hectare production up to 350 quintals
roma: the trees are small and shrubbery and it is suitable for transport because it is long and thick in size. hectare production is 25 tons.
rupali, vaishali, bhagyashree, arka vikas, pusa early dwarf etc. caste is cultivated.']
